tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditionally Exempt / 44th qualifier from Qualifying Tournament, Money List 61-100
tourBios.carHigh: 2011: Made the cut in eight of 23 starts during his rookie season on the Web.com Tour...Picked up his first career top-10 in his 11th start by finishing T4 at the Mexico Open. A 7-under 65 in the third round put him in the final grouping Sunday. An early double bogey and bogey on the front nine kept him out of contention. He wound up shooting 1-under 71 Sunday to finish four strokes behind Erik Compton.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Was the 2009 Pac-10 Player of the Year...Was the 2006 World Junior champion and a member of the Australian Junior team...Missed the cut as an amateur at the 2009 Nationwide Children's Hospital Invitational.
tourBios.personal: His biggest thrill in golf was playing with Greg Norman in the Australian Open...Favorite golf course played is New South Wales GC. Favorite college team is Southern California. Favorite movies are "Anchorman" and "Inception." Favorite book is any from the Harry Potter series. Favorite vacation spots are Hawaii and Fiji. Favorite cities to visit are Las Vegas, New York, Chicago and Sydney...Is an only child.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour in 2012 is T40th at the Chile Classic Presented by Pacific Rubiales.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks T27th in Putting Average on the Web.com Tour.
